            <button class="accordion">Qn. 1: When are payslip emails usually sent out?</button>
            <div class="panel"><p>Payslip emails will typically be sent out by Payday. If you haven't received it a day after Payday, please contact HR.</p></div>

            <button class="accordion">Qn. 2: What is the password for my payslip attachment?</button>
            <div class="panel"><p>The password for your payslip was sent in previous emails from tzpayslip@sunda.com. If you still can't find it, please visit your nearest HR Office for assistance.</p></div>

            <button class="accordion">Qn. 3: I received an email, but the attached payslip doesn't seem to be mine. What should I do?</button>
            <div class="panel"><p>Please DO NOT open the attachment further if it doesn't appear to be yours. Report this immediately to the HR Office so we can rectify the error and ensure data privacy.</p></div>

            <button class="accordion">Qn. 4: The payslip attachment is missing from the email. What should I do?</button>
            <div class="panel"><p>First, ensure you've fully downloaded the attachments. If still not visible, request a resend by contacting HR.</p></div>

            <button class="accordion">Qn. 5: I accidentally deleted the payslip email. How do I get it back?</button>
            <div class="panel"><p>Check your Trash/Bin folder first for recovery. If permanently deleted, visit or contact the HR Office to request a resend.</p></div>

            <button class="accordion">Qn. 6: I entered the password, but I get a "Wrong Password" error. What should I do?</button>
            <div class="panel"><p>Verify you're typing exactly (check for extra spaces, capitalization). If it still fails, visit or contact the HR Office as HR can issue a new password or send an unlocked copy.</p></div>

            <button class="accordion">Qn. 7: If I notice any discrepancies on your payslip, what should I do?</button>
            <div class="panel"><p>If you notice any discrepancies, please visit or contact the HR Office immediately to review your payslip details.</p></div>

            <button class="accordion">Qn. 8: Can I request a printed/stamped copy of my payslip?</button>
            <div class="panel"><p>Yes. Visit your nearest HR Office to request an official printed copy with a stamp.</p></div>

            <button class="accordion">Qn. 9: How can I ensure the payslip email is legitimate?</button>
            <div class="panel"><p>The official payslip email comes from tzpayslip@sunda.com with the subject line "[Month - Year Payslip]" (e.g., January 2025 Payslip). If you suspect phishing, contact HR immediately.</p></div>

            <button class="accordion">Qn. 10: Can I change or customize my Payslip Password?</button>
            <div class="panel"><p>Yes, just visit your nearest HR office and you will be issued with a new password.</p></div>

