                    <td>Taxable Income</td>
                    <td>Gross Salary - Employee NSSF Contribution</td>
                    <td></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>PAYE (Income Tax)</td>
                    <td>Monthly Taxable Income (TZS) ------- Tax Rates(%)<br>0 – 270,000 ----------------------> 0%<br>270,001 – 520,000 ---------------> 8% of amount over 270,000<br>520,001 – 760,000 ---------------> 20,000 + 20% of amount over 520,000<br>760,001 – 1,000,000 -------------> 68,000 + 25% of amount over 760,000<br>Over 1,000,000 ------------------> 128,000 + 30% of amount over 1,000,000</td>
                    <td>See Rates</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>NHIF</td>
                    <td>Employee Contribution: 3% of Basic Salary STD<br>- If 3% of Basic Salary is less than 20,000 → Fixed at 20,000<br>- If 3% of Basic Salary is 20,000 or more → 3% of Basic Salary<br>Employer Contribution: Equal to the employee’s contribution</td>
                    <td>See Rates</td>
                </tr>
